<section class="content-center">
  <h3>"Four Hugs A Day"</h3>
  <p>Family therapist Virginia Satir once said, <b>‚ÄúWe need four hugs a day for survival. We need 8 hugs a day for maintenance. We need 12 hugs a day for growth.‚Äù</b> Satir explains that in order to get by in life, humans require multiple genuine interactions with one another every day. Such a world would be nice. However, with the rise of social media as many individuals‚Äô primary form of communication, the reality is that we have sacrificed the number of interactions we have with others with the quality of each interaction.</p>
  <p>To combat this a couple acquaintances and I decided to build a social media application that encourages more meaningful and genuine interactions between one another. We came up with this idea during the peak of the covid pandemic, where pretty much all face to face interactions were replaced with digital ones. This made it all the more relevant to figure out a way to preserve the fulfilling feeling of having an in person conversation with someone through social media.</p>
  <p>For this project I was the UI/UX lead for our project, as was tasked with leading the design of our frontend components, as well as leading the development of our application client in React Native.</p>
  <img src="/assets/images/fouro/fouro-social-media.jpg" class="medium"/>
</section>
