<section class="content-left">
  <div class="content-left">
    <h3 class="item-left">
      There is a tradeoff...
    </h3>
    <div class="item-right">
      <p>...between the convenience of one-step interactions (like the pressing of a like button or sending a short message), and the authenticity and depth of the interaction. Authentic and genuine interactions take time and effort, which is not always something that people are in the mood for.</p>
      <p>The question for us was how to create a social platform that helps users put more thought and emotion into the messages they send others <b>without</b> making it inconvenient for them to send a message, or make the user feel forced into participating. </p>
      <p>We aimed to tackle this by implementing a messaging platform where users send each other what we coined as <b>‚ÄúDigital Hugs‚Äù</b>, keeping in line with the four hugs a day quote mentioned earlier. We set out to find out how we could enforce meaningful interactions by sending hugs to one another. </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
